	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - A construction worker died on Monday after
falling into a trench at the Blue Hills mall in Midrand, Johannesburg,
emergency medical services said. "We have just discovered a body, being the trapped
body of a 53-year-old man. He was confirmed dead on the scene," said
spokesperson Robert Mulaudzi. Earlier, Mulaudzi said two workers were injured when they
fell into the trench at the mall. One of them was rescued and taken to Sunninghill Hospital
in a critical, but stable condition. The 53-year-old man at that point had not yet been
reached by emergency services.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  